title: SpaceX's Fram2 launch will send civilian crew into first flight around Earth's poles
body: The international all-civilian Fram2 crew is the first in space history to fly to orbit with no licensed pilot or trained astronaut on board.

title: US FAA closes one of two SpaceX Starship probes as rocket remains grounded
body: The U.S. Federal Aviation Administration on Monday said it closed out a review into SpaceX's explosive Starship test flight in January, while another investigation into the rocket's subsequent testing explosion in March remains open.
